@startuml
title Context - Runtime Domains and Control Boundaries
left to right direction

rectangle "Rust Engine Domain" as Rust
rectangle "Binding / Reflection Domain" as Bind
rectangle "Meta-Scripting Domain" as Meta
rectangle "Typed Script Domain" as Script
rectangle "Ctx Graph Domain" as Ctx
rectangle "Capability Runtime Domain" as Cap
rectangle "Bevy ECS Runtime Domain" as ECS
rectangle "USF Runtime State Domain" as USF

Rust -[#1E88E5]-> Bind : exports engine namespaces to Binding/Reflection Domain
Bind -[#1E88E5]-> Meta : exposes bounded meta primitives to Meta-Scripting Domain
Meta -[#1E88E5]-> Script : projects file-type + module rules to Typed Script Domain
Script -[#FB8C00]-> Ctx : navigates script operations via Ctx Graph Domain
Ctx -[#43A047]-> Cap : emits typed capability intents via Capability Runtime Domain
Cap -[#43A047]-> ECS : commits runtime effects in Bevy ECS Runtime Domain
ECS -[#43A047]-> USF : materializes canonical + derived state in USF Runtime State Domain
USF -[#8E24AA]-> Ctx : exposes runtime snapshots back to Ctx Graph Domain
Ctx -[#8E24AA]-> Script : exposes typed read handles back to Typed Script Domain
Rust -[#1E88E5]-> ECS : installs schedule drivers in Bevy ECS Runtime Domain
Rust -[#1E88E5]-> Cap : installs channel backends in Capability Runtime Domain
Rust -[#1E88E5]-> Ctx : installs ctx graph roots and gateways in Ctx Graph Domain
@enduml
